@Jack You are clearly too dumb to understand the purpose of the WTO. If you simply had the time to google it up right now, you would find: 


"The World Trade Organization is an intergovernmental organization that is concerned with the regulation of international trade between nations" 


See how it mentions regulation, but there is no mention of facilitation of trade deals and such? That's because the WTO simply regulates trade: if a country has broken the rules, etc. It has absolutely no say in who trades with who and definitely doesn't just make trade deals with the UK, because, and I have to be very clear here, the WTO only deals with the rules of trade, and is not an economic bloc with members like the EU, ASEAN, etc.

